						<summary>

						<p><hi rend="bold">Hoysaḷa Vira Ramanathadeva, Year 8 = 1262 A.D.</hi></p>						

						<p>Records that a merchant <hi rend="italic">(vāṇigan)</hi> repaired the well (‘the big well built by a merchant’) which had suffered considerable damage from floods and other causes. The well was renamed as Danmatāvaḷan.</p>						

